  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Test-first Performance (TFP) is a testing paradigm that focuses on performance testing from the early stage of&#xD;
    development. For performance oriented applications like a web service, TFP approach can reduce the overall cost of&#xD;
    software testing. Given this potential benefit, TFP is yet to be incorporated in existing cloud testing frameworks.&#xD;
    This paper proposes the design of a testing framework which introduces TFP as a Service (TFPaaS) named as IVRIDIO. It&#xD;
    includes the Plugin for TFP in the Cloud (PTFPC) that will provide instant feedbacks to fix critical performance&#xD;
    issues. To simplify the TFPaaS availing procedure, the Convention over Configuration (CoC) design paradigm has been&#xD;
    applied. A configurable project template is designed using the CoC to maintain TFP test cases. Furthermore, necessary&#xD;
    directions are given to prototype the framework as a testbed for related research.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
